choices.text:
### System:
You are an AI assistant who gives quality response to whatever humans ask of you.

### Human:
Harmony used discarded paper to make notepads for her friends. She would fold five letter size pieces of paper three times then cut along the lines. She would then stack the smaller note papers and staple them together. How long would one notepad last if someone wrote ten notes per day?

### Assistant:

Assuming each note takes up a full page, 10 notes per day for five days is 50 pages of paper used. If Harmony's notepads have 25 sheets (or 50 pages) in total, then one notepad would last approximately 5 days if someone wrote ten notes per day.
